2YP ANALYSIS

NOTE: Data is imported from all_participants.csv

Participants

317 (69% female) students aged 17 to 33 at a public American univeristy participated in the study. All participants completed three tasks: two data analysis scenario (each with a particluar type of temporal interval graph) and a drawing task. In some cases (linear-first), participants (n = 155) completed the first analysis task with a linear model graph, followed by the task with the triangular graph. An additional (n= 162) subjects completed the analysis tasks with graphs in reverse order. Each particiant was randomly assigned to one of five conditions which determined what additional information (scaffold) they received while solving the first five problems on each analysis task: 0-no-scaffold (control), 1-‘what’ text, 2-‘how’-text, 3-static-image, 4-interactive-image. The runtime of the entire study ranged from 22 to 66 minutes (m = 40, sd = 0.48).

  ORDER

In addition, we ran 6 expert participants through two conditions, composed of research assistants with more than 20 hours of experience analyzing data with the triangular model graph.

Explore Runtime

1. Total Runtime
What is the distribution of runtime (for the whole study)? What are the min, max, mean & SD? Are the data normally distributed?

The mean total runtime was approximately 40 minutes, with a standard deviation of 0.48 minutes, with values ranging from 22 to 66 minutes. Should the high and low values be excluded? A Shapiro-Wilk test for normality yielded a value of W = 0.99, 0.01 < p < 0.05, suggesting that the distibution is significantly non-normal, however, the S-W test is known to be biased toward non-normalcy for large samples. The distribution does appear to be slightly positively skewed. Inspection of the QQ-plot reveals that the distribution can be treated as normal for this sample size.

2. Explore Task Runtimes

3. Explore LINEAR TASK Runtime by Graph Order
What is the distribution of runtime for the linear model task and triangular model task for each level of the graph-order factor? What are the min, max, mean & SD?

The mean runtime for the linear model task is 9.2 minutes, with a standard deviation of 2.5 minutes, and values ranging from 3.92 to 23.06 minutes. Participant with value of 3.9 minutes is suspicious, review for exclusion.
